link: According to the Chinese Freedom of Information Act 1 , an annual report on the FOI performance should be published before the end of January of the next year. The report should cover how well the agency or public-funded institution proactively disclose information, how well it responded to request and include other key performance issues.  In 2019, after the update of Freedom of Information Act, the State Council issued a new standard for publishing annual performance report 2 which details how information regarding with responding to requests should be reported and broken down into the type of requesters and the type of reasons to not releasing information or reasons to not be able to respond or reasons to not process request. The report should also cover the num of appealing cases and final result of appealing.   The Notice on Publication of Annual Freedom of Information Work Report requires that each agency, department or other type of government entities should be responsible for timely and high-quality data reporting and ensure data are verifiable.   The 2020 annual report published by all public entities is the latest but also the first version of annual report following the suggested guidance.
